	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Wednesday&#44; 17th of Hesvan &#40;Nov&#41;&#44; 1865</date>.</p>
				<p>Peace and all good forever&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">To this day I am without a word from you. My low spirits in&#45;<lb/>crease from day to day. Herewith you will receive the beautiful article<lb/> about which you must certainly be thinking and in which my honest prin&#45;<lb/>ciples are expressed.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You would be doing a great kindness if you could print it<lb/> also in German with English letters&#44; but in any case it must be transla&#45;<lb/>ted. Perhaps you would have printed several hundred copies of the article<lb/> as a circular&#44; in order that it might be more widely spread over the land.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I feel very unhappy here. I have the notion to have my<lb/> &#8220;<persName>Esther</persName>&#8221; printed there and to stay there during the printing&#44; and give<lb/> there lectures about history and religion. That should bring something<lb/> in.  In this way I could support and encourage your efforts with regard<lb/> to the seminary. The honor belongs to you. I had enough of it at home.<lb/> Here it is a case of &#8220;He who increases knowledge increases pain&#8221;. Here<lb/> one must be either a <persName>Wise</persName> or&#44; on the other hand&#44; an <persName>Illoway</persName>. Both of them<lb/> &#8220;This one as he understands it and this one as he understands it&#8221;&#44; but<lb/> they are alike in character.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I tell you this idea in secret&#44; and if you agree&#44; I shall<lb/> write to <persName>Weiler</persName> and <persName>Ellis</persName>...... I must work openly&#44; otherwise I shall<lb/> be destroyed &#44; God forbid&#44; As a friend of six years&#39; standing&#44; you owe<lb/> it to me who never changed his word&#44;  just as you owe it to me who never changed his word&#44; just as you owe it to the Torah<lb/> that is in me&#44; to do everything possible. &#8220;A prisoner cannot release<lb/> himself from the prison&#8221;.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">As soon as you have translated the article&#44; I want the<lb/> manuscript. I should also very much like to see the proof sheet of<lb/> the English. The matter is too important. A word incorrectly put<lb/> may be injurious.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What I told you today is <sic>avery</sic> great secret under the great&#45;<lb/>est seal of silence.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">With sincere respect&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Your friend and admirer&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName></p>
				<p>I may not see or near any one here.</p>
		</body>
